         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">21/1/90 ¶  ¶ In my presidential speech, noble friend, for the Melbourne meeting of the great Australian ¶  Association for the Advancement of Science, I have mentioned especially that an illustrated m...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">90.01.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Nordstedt</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Handskr. avdl., Universitetsbibliotek, Lund.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">21/1/90</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In meiner Präsidenten-Rede, edler Freund, für die Melbourne Versammlung der grossen australian Association for the Advancement of Science, habe ich besonders erwähnt, dass eine illustrirte Monographie der Characeen die nöthigste jetzt im Pflanzenreich wäre! Könnten </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Sie</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> mit </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Subsidien</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> von hier eine solche aus dem reichen Schatz Ihrer Erfahrungen liefern. Die ganze botanische Welt wäre dabei interessirt u. die australische ganz besonders. Vielleicht könnten Sie einen Band herstellen, der sich in Form u. Behandlung denen der Eucalypten, Acacien, Myoporinen, Salsolaceen und dem bald zu beginnenden über Candolleaceen anschloss, so dass jede Platte nur </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">eine</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Art enthalte. Was müssten die Hilfsmittel geldlich für den Zweck sein? um dies auszuführen </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Ihnen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> wäre die Durchführung leicht, so dass solch ein Band </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">bald</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> erscheinen könnte.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Sie ehrend</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21/1/90</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>In my presidential speech, noble friend, for the Melbourne meeting of the great Australian<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. Australasian. </p>
               </note> Association for the Advancement of Science, I have mentioned especially that an illustrated monograph of the <name key="Characeae">Characeae</name> would be the most necessary thing now in the plant kingdom!<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B90.13.01, p. 15.</p>
               </note> Could <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">you</hi>
               </seg> produce such a thing from the rich store of your experience with <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">subsidy</hi>
               </seg> from here. The whole botanical world would be interested in it and the Australian quite particularly. Perhaps you could produce a volume that in form and treatment followed those of the Eucalypts, <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>s, <name key="Myoporinae">Myoporinae</name>, <name key="Salsolaceae">Salsolaceae</name> and that soon to be begun on the <name key="Candollaceae">Candollaceae</name>,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Mueller's publications, respectively B79.13.11 and following decades; B87.13.14 and B88.13.11; B86.08.05; B89.13.11 and following decades; B93.02.04.</p>
               </note> so that each plate contained only <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               </seg> species. What would the pecuniary assistance have to be for the purpose in order to carry this out? The implementation would be easy <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">for you</hi>
               </seg>, so that such a volume could come out <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">soon</hi>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Nordstedt took up M's proposal, the work being published as Nordstedt (1891), but no further decades were published.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
